{
  "text": "For Maxwell's equations, there is a necessary solvability condition given by the continuity equation for currents and charges (Eq. [CITATION_1] in the cylindrically symmetric TE case). Partition of the RHS (38) may break the continuity, that's why for the numerical tests of Section 3 we have chosen zero charges and solenoidal currents (37a), (37b) that satisfy the continuity equation identically. As far as the more general framework outlined in Section 4, it has been shown in [CITATION_2] that the auxiliary sources on X n X e , see Fig. 10 , can also be obtained in the form of solenoidal currents and zero charges. Hence, they can withstand partition [CITATION_3] with no violation of continuity.",
